The nature of the research. Study protocol. Structure of research paper. Publication and review of research papers. Evaluation of researchers. Oral and poster presentation of research findings. Searching and saving scientific information by using Mendeley reference management software. Master's thesis and its writing. Citing, creating a list of references. Typical errors in studies.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give basic knowledge in conducting a research study, and presenting and publishing the study results.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After working through this course students are able:   - to write a skeleton protocol for a study to investigate a specific question in a specific setting; - to present research findings following the main parts of a scientific paper/main rules of oral and poster presentation;  - to search information and to use reference management software; - to follow instructions for writing of Master thesis
